        <mj-text font-family="verdana, Arial" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:700;">Boy Missing Since 1951 Reunited With Family After 72 Years</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text font-family="verdana, Arial" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Avenir Next',Avenir,'Helvetica Neue',Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,'Segoe ui',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.6;">Luis Armando Albino, who was kidnapped from a California playground in 1951, has been reunited with his family after more than 70 years. As a child, Luis was lured away by a woman and raised by another family on the East Coast. Despite extensive searches, he remained missing for decades.
          </p <p style="font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Avenir Next',Avenir,'Helvetica Neue',Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,'Segoe ui',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.6;"><a href="https://people.com/luis-albino-kidnapped-seventy-years-ago-found-living-grandfather-8717785" target="_blank">The case</a> was reignited when Luis’ niece, Alida Alequin, took a DNA test and matched with him, leading to a long-awaited reunion. After DNA confirmation, Luis was reunited with his terminally ill brother Roger and other family members. The emotional reunion has brought closure to a case that had puzzled investigators for decades.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding-top="20px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
